# Create SequenceView Wrapper Component

## Overview
Create a high-level wrapper component around `SequenceGridRenderer` that handles canvas sizing, window resize events, and keyboard shortcut bindings for sequence navigation.

## Component Location
- **NEW**: `packages/web/src/components/SequenceView.tsx`

## Component Responsibilities

### Canvas Sizing & Layout
- Measure container dimensions using `ResizeObserver` or `useElementSize` hook
- Pass dimensions to SequenceGridRenderer as props
- Handle aspect ratio and responsive sizing
- Ensure canvas fits within allocated space
- Account for scrollbars and padding

### Resize Event Handling
- Listen for window resize events
- Debounce resize handling (150-250ms)
- Recalculate visible rows/columns on resize
- Maintain scroll position relative to content
- Smooth transitions during resize

### Keyboard Shortcut Integration
Bind sequence navigation shortcuts:
- `h/←`: Scroll left
- `l/→`: Scroll right  
- `j/↓`: Scroll down
- `k/↑`: Scroll up
- `Ctrl+f`: Page down
- `Ctrl+b`: Page up
- `g` + `g`: Jump to start
- `G`: Jump to end
- `/`: Enter search mode
- `n`: Next search result
- `N`: Previous search result
- `v`: Toggle view mode (DNA/AA)
- `1-6`: Select reading frame (in AA mode)

### Store Connection
```typescript
const setScrollPosition = useAppStore(state => state.setScrollPosition);
const toggleViewMode = useAppStore(state => state.toggleSequenceViewMode);
const setReadingFrame = useAppStore(state => state.setReadingFrame);
const jumpToPosition = useAppStore(state => state.jumpToPosition);
```

### Component Structure
```typescript
interface SequenceViewProps {
  className?: string;
  onPositionChange?: (position: number) => void;
}

export const SequenceView: React.FC<SequenceViewProps> = (props) => {
  // Container ref for size measurement
  const containerRef = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null);

  // Measure container size
  const { width, height } = useElementSize(containerRef);

  // Handle resize
  useEffect(() => {
    // Resize logic
  }, [width, height]);

  // Keyboard shortcuts
  useKeyboardShortcuts({
    // Shortcut definitions
  });

  return (
    <div ref={containerRef} className={props.className}>
      <SequenceGridRenderer 
        width={width}
        height={height}
        // ... other props
      />
    </div>
  );
};
```

## Integration Points
- Wrap SequenceGridRenderer with sizing logic
- Connect to keyboard event system
- Integrate with layout system (Header/Footer/Sidebar)
- Handle focus management

## Edge Cases
- Handle very small container sizes
- Graceful degradation when no sequence loaded
- Prevent shortcut conflicts with other views
- Handle rapid resize events efficiently

## Accessibility
- Focus management for keyboard navigation
- ARIA labels for screen readers
- Skip-to-content functionality
- Keyboard trap prevention

## Testing Checklist
- [ ] Canvas resizes correctly with window
- [ ] All keyboard shortcuts work as expected
- [ ] Shortcuts only active when component focused
- [ ] Resize debouncing prevents performance issues
- [ ] Scroll position maintained during resize
- [ ] Component integrates with layout system
- [ ] Focus states work correctly

